data.name: TrainingPlanHtml_LegendContent
data.value: MFMuscle failure. You should do as many reps as you can until you cannot do more MAXYou should do as many reps as you can do correctly WVery light warm up set. AMAlmost max. You should do almost maximum reps (max-1 for example) XYou should do X reps (for example 10) and finish this set. -XYou should do maximum X reps and finish this set. For example -10 means that you should do maximum 10 reps (or less) X-You should do minimum X reps. For example 10- means that you should do minimum 10 reps (or more). X-YYou should do minimum X and maximum Y reps. You finish the current set when you reach the maximum number or you don't have strength to do more. For example 10-12 means that you should do minimum 10 and maximum 12 reps. ^ZDrop set. Z means how many drops we have, for example ^2 means that for this set you will have 2 additional drops of weight 8-10^1This value means that you do minimum 8 and maximum 10 reps. After this you drop some weight (drop set) and you do next repetitions.
